<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFCA1907FF6CFC12FE72C56D" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCA1907FF6CFC12FE72C56D" blockId="3.[178,1085,993,1103]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">
Comment: The original description is based on a male 
<typeStatus id="54BD8847FFCA1907FC93FC12FC2AC2D5" box="[845,934,993,1015]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">holotype</typeStatus>
and a female 
<typeStatus id="54BD8847FFCA1907FF6CFC0CFE85C536" box="[178,265,1023,1044]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">paratype</typeStatus>
from &quot;Yentchan, main River, 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F807FFCA1907FD89FC0CFD1FC537" box="[599,659,1023,1045]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West Sepik" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">Sepik</collectingRegion>
&quot; and 
<specimenCount id="9D00FD6CFFCA1907FD06FC0CFCFBC536" box="[728,887,1023,1045]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">three paratypes</specimenCount>
from &quot;Blackwater River, 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F807FFCA1907FF29FBEFFEBFC510" box="[247,307,1052,1074]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="West Sepik" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">Sepik</collectingRegion>
&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B14FFCA1907FE97FBEFFE31C510" author="LAST H" box="[329,445,1052,1074]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" pagination="109 - 125" refId="ref7323" refString="LAST H. (1984): Recorded and new species of Coleoptera (Staphylinidae, Paederinae) in Papua New Guinea. - Folia Entomologica Hungarica 45 (2): 109 - 125." type="journal article" year="1984">LAST 1984</bibRefCitation>
). An examination of the above 
<specimenCount id="9D00FD6CFFCA1907FD22FBEFFC05C513" box="[764,905,1052,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">two paratypes</specimenCount>
revealed that this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCA1907FEAEFBCAFE74C56C" authorityName="CASEY" authorityYear="1905" box="[368,504,1081,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCA1907FEAEFBCAFE74C56C" box="[368,504,1081,1102]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">Pseudolathra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFCA1900FF6CFBADFD66C71C" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1155" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCA1907FF6CFBADFC66C5CB" blockId="3.[178,1085,1118,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">
Redescription: Small species; body length 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFCA1907FD0BFBACFCC2C556" box="[725,846,1119,1140]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="4.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="4.8" valueMin="4.4">4.4-4.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFCA1907FBC3FBACFF50C5B3" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body blackish-brown to blackish, with the posterior margins of the abdominal segments VII and VIII broadly reddish-yellow, distinctly contrasting with the remainder of the body; legs yellowish; antennae brown, with the apical 2-4 antennomeres, antennomere I, and the bases of the remaining antennomeres pale-reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCA1907FF6CFB0AFC10C445" blockId="3.[178,1085,1273,1383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">
Head (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCA1907FF28FB0AFEBDC42D" box="[246,305,1273,1295]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[185,1078,212,1212]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-5: Pseudolathra sepikensis (LAST), paratype: (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4-5) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as broad as long, subparallel behind eyes; punctation coarse and sparse on dorsal surface, median dorsal portion more or less extensively impunctate; microsculpture absent. Eyes large, distinctly longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna slender, 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFCA1907FE38FAA2FDD7C444" box="[486,603,1361,1382]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.7">1.7-1.8 mm</quantity>
long; all antennomeres oblong.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCA1907FF6CFA85FC50C4C6" blockId="3.[178,1085,1398,1508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCA1907FEFAFA85FED2C4AE" box="[292,350,1398,1420]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[185,1078,212,1212]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-5: Pseudolathra sepikensis (LAST), paratype: (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4-5) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1154">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) short, 1.06-1.09 times as long as broad and 1.00-1.02 times as broad as head; lateral margins nearly straight in anterior two-thirds in dorsal view; dorsal series composed of approximately 11-14 macropunctures; midline broadly impunctate; laterad of dorsal series with rather sparse and coarse punctation; microsculpture absent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF79666DFFCD1900FF6CFB35FB9DC5D0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155" startId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" targetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCD1900FF6CFB35FB9DC5D0" blockId="4.[178,1085,1222,1267]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FF6CFB35FE8DC5F9" bold="true" box="[178,257,1222,1244]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Figs 1-5</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCD1900FED1FB35FDBAC5F9" authority="(LAST)" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Last" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[271,566,1222,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepikensis">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FED1FB35FE61C5F9" box="[271,493,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Pseudolathra sepikensis</emphasis>
(LAST)
</taxonomicName>
, paratype: (
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FD78FB35FD3DC5F9" bold="true" box="[678,689,1222,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">1</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FCF6FB35FCBFC5F9" bold="true" box="[808,819,1222,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">2</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FC28FB35FB8DC5F9" bold="true" box="[1014,1025,1222,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">3</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCD1900FEEBFB2EFEDFC5D0" bold="true" box="[309,339,1245,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">4-5</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCD1900FF6CFAF3FC18C46F" blockId="4.[178,1085,1279,1358]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Elytra (Fig. 1) 1.04-1.06 times as long as pronotum; epipleural line absent (lateral view); punctation rather fine, arranged in series. Hind wings fully developed. Metatarsomere I slightly longer than II. Protarsomeres I-IV strongly dilated in both sexes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCD1900FF6CFAAFFDE5C4E7" blockId="4.[178,1085,1372,1478]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Abdomen as broad as, or narrower than elytra; punctation very dense and very fine, somewhat sparser on tergite VII than on tergites III-VI, sparse on tergite VIII; interstices with microreticulation, matt; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII strongly convex.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCD1900FF19FA27FD66C71C" blockId="4.[178,1085,1492,1598]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">
: sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCD1900FEBDFA27FE2FC4C8" box="[355,419,1492,1514]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[185,1078,212,1212]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-5: Pseudolathra sepikensis (LAST), paratype: (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4-5) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse and with weakly modified pubescence, posterior margin weakly concave; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCD1900FD60FA03FC8CC724" box="[702,768,1520,1542]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[185,1078,212,1212]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-5: Pseudolathra sepikensis (LAST), paratype: (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4-5) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse, posterior excision U-shaped; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCD1900FE35F9FFFDCFC703" box="[491,579,1547,1570]" captionStart="Figs 1-5" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[186,1070,212,1199]" captionTargetId="figure-1@4.[185,1078,212,1212]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-5: Pseudolathra sepikensis (LAST), paratype: (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII; (4-5) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-5: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307620/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155">Figs 4-5</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="4CFE9B00FFCD1900FD8CF9F8FD22C703" box="[594,686,1547,1569]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="1155" unit="mm" value="0.85">0.85 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process subapically with pronounced tooth; dorsal plate long, thin, and lamellate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFCC1901FF6CFF28FF78C0DA" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCC1901FF6CFF28FF78C0DA" blockId="5.[178,1086,219,504]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">
Comparative notes: Characters suggesting a closer relationship to any of the species known from the Oriental and Palaearctic regions were not found. 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCC1901FF6CFEE6FE2AC008" box="[178,422,277,298]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sepikense">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCC1901FF6CFEE6FE2AC008" box="[178,422,277,298]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Pseudolathra sepikense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by numerous characters, particularly its small body size, the absence of an epipleural line, the shape of the male sternite VIII, and the morphology of the aedeagus. The absence of an epipleural line is remarkable, since the presence of such a line was previously considered one of the main characters distinguishing 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCC1901FECAFE79FE10C0BD" authorityName="CASEY" authorityYear="1905" box="[276,412,394,415]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pseudolathra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCC1901FECAFE79FE10C0BD" box="[276,412,394,415]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Pseudolathra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCC1901FE3DFE79FCCDC082" authority="GRAVENHORST, 1802" authorityName="GRAVENHORST" authorityYear="1802" box="[483,833,394,416]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCC1901FE3DFE79FDD6C0BD" box="[483,602,394,415]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Lathrobium</emphasis>
GRAVENHORST, 1802
</taxonomicName>
and some other lathrobiine genera. Interestingly, an analogous reduction of the epipleural line was observed also in one species group of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D66FFCC1901FE01FE36FCDFC0F8" authority="MULSANT &amp; REY, 1878" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1878" box="[479,851,453,474]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B972EAF7FFCC1901FE01FE36FDDAC0F8" box="[479,598,453,474]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Lobrathium</emphasis>
MULSANT &amp; REY, 1878
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F3117675FFCC1901FC4AFE36FC6CC0F9" box="[916,992,453,475]" name="Taiwan" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B14FFCC1901FC2EFE36FF65C0DA" author="ASSING V" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" pagination="301 - 361" refId="ref6939" refString="ASSING V. (2010): On the Lathrobiina of Taiwan (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 60 (2): 301 - 361." type="journal article" year="2010">ASSING 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31C656EFFCC1901FF6CFDFBFC29C37A" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB936E5FFCC1901FF6CFDFBFC29C37A" blockId="5.[178,1085,520,600]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">
Distribution and natural history: The 
<typeStatus id="54BD8847FFCC1901FC93FDFBFCFDC33F" box="[845,881,520,541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">type</typeStatus>
locality is a river basin in the north of 
<collectingCountry id="F3117675FFCC1901FE54FDD6FDDCC319" box="[394,592,549,571]" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="133D2A60FFCC1901FD80FDD6FD28C319" box="[606,676,549,571]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="13.[178,223,1482,1503]" captionTargetBox="[178,1083,859,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-38@13.[178,1083,859,1464]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of Pseudolathra armata (black triangles), P. bisinuata (star), P. sepikensis (white circle), P. naviculum (black circle), P. puncta (white triangle), and P. cyanea (diamond)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5307636" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5307636/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">Map 2</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EF974B14FFCC1901FC98FDD6FC45C319" author="LAST H" box="[838,969,549,571]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156" pagination="109 - 125" refId="ref7323" refString="LAST H. (1984): Recorded and new species of Coleoptera (Staphylinidae, Paederinae) in Papua New Guinea. - Folia Entomologica Hungarica 45 (2): 109 - 125." type="journal article" year="1984">LAST (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, two of the 
<typeStatus id="54BD8847FFCC1901FF6CFDB0FF52C37A" box="[178,222,579,600]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1156">type</typeStatus>
specimens were collected in &quot;aquatic vegetation by a swampy creek&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
